      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I hear how profoundly valid your frustration is when advice feels dismissive of real grief; losing that sense of self tied to external validation is a form of loss. Instead of \"finding\" a lost person, perhaps the work involves gently allowing yourself to mourn the loss of that former identity as something tangible. A therapist who specializes in existential issues or trauma might be better suited to meet you where you are without offering platitudes. Prioritize finding a space where you can validate that this loss is real, not just an unmet need for surface-level fixes.",
      "source": "target",
